            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>What facilities does CVG offer for travellers?</h3>
            <p>CVG features a modern terminal with one main building and two concourses, providing a total of 51 gates. Travelers can easily navigate the airport using the underground moving walkway and people mover, ensuring a smooth transition between concourses. The terminal is designed to enhance passenger comfort and convenience, making it easy to access amenities before your flight.</p>
            <h3>Where do international arrivals go?</h3>
            <p>All international flights without pre-clearance procedures are directed to Concourse B. This dedicated area is equipped with customs and border protection facilities, allowing travelers to efficiently process their arrivals. Passengers arriving from abroad can expect streamlined processing to help minimize wait times and ensure a pleasant arrival experience.</p>
            <h3>Are there any art installations in the airport?</h3>
            <p>Absolutely! CVG is home to 14 striking Art Deco murals created by Winold Reiss, originally located in the Cincinnati Union Terminal. These murals, depicting local workers and cultural themes, are thoughtfully placed throughout the terminal, adding a unique artistic flair to your travel experience. Additionally, you can find various pieces of Charley Harper artwork in the Concourse B food court, further enriching the airport's artistic ambiance.</p>
            <h3>What cargo operations are conducted at CVG?</h3>
            <p>Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport serves as a significant cargo hub, being the largest global hub for DHL and the primary hub for Amazon Air. The airport has seen substantial investments to expand its cargo operations, contributing to its status as the 4th busiest airport in North America based on cargo tonnage. This robust infrastructure supports numerous daily flights, facilitating both domestic and international cargo movement.</p>
            <h3>How accessible is CVG for passengers?</h3>
            <p>CVG is designed with passenger convenience in mind, featuring a single terminal layout that simplifies navigation. The underground moving walkway provides direct access to both concourses without the need to step outside, which is especially beneficial during inclement weather. This thoughtful design enhances the overall travel experience, making it easy for passengers to reach their gates efficiently.</p>
            <h3>Are there dining and shopping options available at the airport?</h3>
            <p>Yes, travelers at CVG can enjoy a diverse range of dining and retail options throughout the terminal. From local eateries serving regional cuisine to shops offering travel essentials, there’s something for everyone. Whether you’re looking to grab a quick bite before your flight or browse for souvenirs, the airport’s offerings cater to various tastes and preferences.</p>
            <h3>What should I know about security and check-in procedures?</h3>
